tradeR

Last update: 2019-05-25 09:31:02 in Europe/London

library("rjson")

Fetch prices

# Look for files of interest
files <- list.files(path = "tmp", pattern = "*.json", full.names = TRUE)
stopifnot(length(files) > 0)
extract <- function(f){
  paste("reading", f)
  raw = fromJSON(file = f)
  p <- c(); for (observation in raw$Data) p <- c(p, observation$close)
  p
}

prices <- as.data.frame(mapply(extract, files))

Linear regression

for (y in prices) {

  # Do linear regression
  x <- 1:length(y)
  relation <- lm(y ~ x)

  plot(x, y, col = "darkgreen", main = "hi", 
    abline(relation, col="red"), xlab = "minutes", ylab = "USD")
}

Normalise

# Take a copy to normalise
n = prices

for (y in n) {
  low = min(y)
  high = max(y)

  y = y - low
  y = y / (high - low)
}

matplot(n, pch = 1)
